---
description: Luau strict typing standards
alwaysApply: true
---

Add `--!strict` to the top of all Luau files.
Adhere to strict typing in all Luau files.
Add explicit type annotations to all variable declarations, even when the type is obvious from context.
Example: `local count: number = 1`
Exception: when requiring a module used elsewhere that does not expose an explicit type, you may annotate that required module as `any`.
Prefer annotating top-level module tables created in the same file and returned by that module script as `any` (for example `local BootstrapLoader: any = {}`).
Follow the Luau styling guide referenced in project docs.
Do not define reusable config or contract types via `typeof(SomeConstant)` when a canonical exported type already exists.
Prefer importing shared exported types from `src/shared/Types/*` for cross-file contracts.
Prefer lower camel case for user-defined function and method names (for example `setCFrame`, `createForModel`).
Keep constructor names as `new` when using a class-like module pattern.
Use PascalCase for Roblox engine API members and Roblox types only.
